OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA cold, but sunny start to the
OL,6,Fday. Cloud then building to bring a
OL,7,Ffew showers from mid morning but many
OL,8,Fplaces staying dry, with further sunny
OL,9,Fspells later.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA mainly dry evening with
OL,12,Flate sunny spells, though turning
OL,13,Fquickly rather chilly. Mainly dry for
OL,14,Fthe rest of the night with clear
OL,15,Fspells leading to a risk of frost.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FA touch of frost first
OL,18,Fthing in the morning for some. The
OL,19,Frest of the day will then be dry,
OL,20,Fbright and partly cloudy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
